  For purposes of the following three paragraphs, a "patent license"
is any express agreement or commitment, however denominated, not to
enforce a patent (such as an express permission to practice a patent
or covenant not to sue for patent infringement).  To "grant" such a
patent license to a party means to make such an agreement or
commitment not to enforce a patent against the party.

  If you convey a covered work, knowingly relying on a patent license,
and the Corresponding Source of the work is not available for anyone
